HEADWORD: Tchick
<hw>Tchick</hw> <pr>(ch⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Imitative.]</ety> <def>A slight sound such as that made by
pressing the tongue against the roof of the mouth and explosively
sucking out the air at one side, as in urging on a horse.</def> --
<def2><pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make a tchick.</def></def2><-- = cluck?
click? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

